snippet.textDisplay:
The fact that they claimed the plastic layer is just a protection layer is ridiculous!
It’s not protecting any screen! It’s the SCREEN! If it’s a protection layer, the phone should be able to function without it, but....no!

The Z Flip is a great move of Samsung, but the fact that they over-advertised this model just kinda overwhelmed all of that. The screen can be scratched with your nails, and the price to repair the screen is $120(?) or $400(?). That’s ridiculous!
I like the fact that it is compact, which perfect for us girls as we have clutches and small bags. But honestly I would rather go for the Galaxy Fold! It’s just simply more impressive. You get the screen size of a tablet but in the size of a normal phone. Here is normal screen size but in the size of a square(?), when you open it up, it's not fun anymore. Idk if you guys understand what I mean😅😅😅
As I say, I was very impressed with this model of Samsung, but they should have used most of their time and effort for the screen display instead of over-advertised their phone.

I think everybody would prefer glass over plastic. Everything about it just better🤷‍♀️
